A bit more background: when I was much younger, PUA culture was just becoming a thing, and I found a lot of it extremely helpful. I was fascinated when I read The Game
, but was turned off by the fakery and spectacle of some of the more flamboyant techniques (e.g. the whole Mystery Method
). But there were also people in that community that emphasised the 'natural art of seduction', e.g., making yourself more attractive and finding straightforward ways for making romantic first encounters with women run smoothly.
